11/11/2004
NEW YORK, United States -- UN Secretary General Kofi Annan has initiated consultations on the name dispute between Greece and Macedonia, according to media reports Wednesday (10 November). 
Annan reportedly met with Greece's Permanent Representative to the UN, Adamantios Vasilakis, to discuss Athens' plans regarding the recent US recognition of Macedonia's constitutional name. 
UN diplomatic sources say Annan also intends to meet with representatives from Skopje. 
He reportedly is urging both sides to continue UN-sponsored bilateral negotiations aimed at resolving the issue. 
(ANA - 11/11/04; A1 TV - 10/11/04)
